## What Cascade does NOT do

- Does not bypass canon to ship faster
- Does not store production credentials in development environments
- Does not introduce new dependencies, fonts, colors, or design patterns without explicit operator approval logged in `decisions_log.md`
- Does not write copy without an explicit brief
- Does not "improve" copy that's been provided in a brief
- Does not introduce parallel V2 versions of components when one caller exists
- Does not ship lorem ipsum, placeholder text, or stock photography
- Does not load third-party scripts beyond what's in `decisions_log.md`
- Does not draft client-facing communications of any kind

